{
  "stem": "11744.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was there with my children and stayed there, and that's where I-- I trained these nurses.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then when everybody had to go, and we had an exit or something through France, when the entire French people went down south to try to avoid the Germans who were coming down from the north.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were-- they were-- they were filling the roads in such a way that-- that the older tanks and the French army could not even try to go and to defend themselves, because the whole population of France was-- was closing the roads.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But at that time, I was assigned to a certain town where I was supposed to meet the doctors and a surgeon I had been with before when I was on the Maginot Line.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were supposed to take care of behind the scene of the wounded soldiers who would be coming down, who would be sent down in ambulance.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, there wasn't very much wounded, but I was all by myself.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My-- my ambulance-- we called that an ambulance, we put the people in-- the nurse, the surgeon, the doctors.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My ambulance was stuck behind the line that the German made of France.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They separated France in two.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I was alone, and had 500 wounded soldiers in a school that had transformed into a hospital, and was alone for four days with them.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My husband was taken in the north of France when the-- the 10th of June, when the Germans invaded from Belgium through-- through the northern part of France, and he was part of one battalion who fell in their hands.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And life was so terrible at that time that all the top-- the top rank officers had left.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
